cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the implementation of a cryptographic primitive (one-time program) using the Trusted Execution Environment of modern CPUs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of a software system (two flavours of OTP system) using TEE. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possible category as the paper discusses the performance profiles of the two OTP systems. 
- cs.AR (Architecture) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of TEE in modern CPUs to realize OTP functionality. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on programming languages specifically, but rather on the implementation of OTP using TEE.
